{"TOXALBUMIN":[{"def":"Any of a class of toxic substances of protein nature; a toxin.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to poison; poisonous; as, toxic medicines.","pos":""}],"TOXICANT":[{"def":"A poisonous agent or drug, as opium; an intoxicant.","pos":""}],"TOXICITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being toxic or poisonous; poisonousness.","pos":""}],"TOXICOGENIC":[{"def":"Producing toxic products; as, toxicogenic germs or bacteria.","pos":""}],"TOXICOLOGICAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to toxicology.","pos":""}],"TOXICOLOGIST":[{"def":"One versed in toxicology; the writer of a treatise on poisons.","pos":""}],"TOXICOLOGY":[{"def":"The science which treats of poisons, their effects, antidotes, and recignition; also, a discourse or treatise on the science.","pos":""}],"TOXICOMANIA":[{"def":"An insane desire for intoxicating or poisonous drugs, as alcohol or opium.","pos":""}],"TOXIFERA":[{"def":"Same as Toxoglossa.","pos":"noun"},{"def":"A poisonous product formed by pathogenic bacteria, as a toxic proteid or poisonous ptomaine.","pos":"noun"}],"TOXIPHOBIA":[{"def":"An insane or greatly exaggerated dread of poisons.","pos":""}],"TOXODON":[{"def":"A gigantic extinct herbivorous mammal from South America, having teeth bent like a bow.","pos":""}],"TOXODONTA":[{"def":"An extinct order of Mammalia found in the South American Tertiary formation.","pos":"noun"}],"TOXOGLOSSA":[{"def":"A division of marine gastropod mollusks in which the radula are converted into poison fangs.","pos":"noun"}],"TOXOID":[{"def":"An altered form of a toxin, possessing little or no toxic power.","pos":""}],"TOXOPHILITE":[{"def":"A lover of archery; one devoted to archery.","pos":""}],"TOXOTES":[{"def":"A genus of fishes comprising the archer fishes.","pos":""}]}